<hl>
<seg id=1> Chinese enterprises became the biggest foreign investor in Macao. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Macao, 3 April, by Wang Zhigen, Che Yuming Zhang Xuming, President of Chinese Enterprise Association in Macao, said that at present, there were about 200 Chinese enterprises in Macao, and the total investment exceeded 90 billion Macao Yuan. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese enterprises became the biggest foreign investor in Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In the Fifth Anniversary Party of Chinese Enterprise Association in Macao yesterday, Zhang Xuming said that in Macao the enterprises of mainland investment developed from the small to the big, from the weak to the strong, and became an important part of the economy of Macao. </seg>
<seg id=5> They made a great contribution to the prosperity and stability of Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It's reported that in the areas of trade, industry, finance, insurance, tourism, food, traffic and transport, construction, etc., these enterprises participated extensively in the management activities. </seg>
<seg id=7> Among them, the Chinese capital made up 50% of the finance and insurance, 50-70% of the tourism, 31% of the value of export and import, and 70% of the real estate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Zhang Xuming made clear that the Chinese enterprises in Macao would continue following Deng Xiaoping's constructive thought of "one country, two systems" and the government's policies for Hong Kong and Macao. They would adhere to the principle of "what to do, and what not to do". Working together with the local people of the business circles, they would devote themselves to the economic stability and the social development of Macao. </seg>
</p>
